Kaisa Kaunonen wrote:
&gt; Hi,
&gt;
&gt; there&#39;s a badly planned web site which pushes all sorts of rubbish to
&gt; our archive while being crawled with Heritrix. The version is 1.6.0
&gt; out of the box (don&#39;t know if version number matters here)
&gt;
&gt; In logs there are entries like these, for example.
&gt;
&gt; http://www.mattivanhanen.net/index.php?sivu=mvmpvapa&PHPSESSID=94eedeccc2275891fd6bb0a8e386806c&l=fi&l=fi&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se 
&gt; &lt;http://www.mattivanhanen.net/index.php?sivu=mvmpvapa&PHPSESSID=94eedeccc2275891fd6bb0a8e386806c&l=fi&l=fi&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&gt;
&gt; http://www.mattivanhanen.net/index.php?sivu=kirjakauppa&PHPSESSID=94eedeccc2275891fd6bb0a8e386806c&l=fi&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&l=se 
&gt; &lt;http://www.mattivanhanen.net/index.php?sivu=kirjakauppa&PHPSESSID=94eedeccc2275891fd6bb0a8e386806c&l=fi&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&l=fi&l=se&l=se&gt;
&gt;
&gt; In the settings
&gt;
&gt; pathological path filter is enabled, with repetitions=3
&gt; (should be repetitions=2 in order to have an effect here)
&gt; and in uri-canonicalization-rules, SessionIDs = enabled
&gt;
&gt; I thought that PHPSESSID is among the known session ids by default?
It is.  Are you seeing Heritrix crawling pages that except for sessionid 
are the same? (The session id continues to show in URLs recorded in 
crawl.log.  Canonicalization rules strip the session id from an URL 
before it gets stored to the internal set of already seen URLs).

Looking at pathological path filter, it looks like it works only where 
the &#39;/&#39; character delimits repetitions: 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/filter/PathologicalPathFilter.html#53 
(REGEX_PREFIX and REGEX_SUFFIX are sandwiched around whatever  you set 
for the &#39;repetitions&#39; count).

You might try adding an override for this site only with a custom regex 
filter to match runaway URLs like those  pasted above.

Yours,
St.Ack
